text: The Rosedale Plantation is a plantation in Vaughn, Yazoo County, Mississippi. ==History== The cottage was built circa 1870 for Milton Cyrus Ewing and his wife, Augusta Anderson.National Register of Historic Places nomination form It burned down in 1891, but it was rebuilt shortly after. ==Heritage significance== It has been listed on the National Register of Historic Places since July 20, 2011. ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in Mississippi Category:Houses in Yazoo County, Mississippi Category:Plantations in Mississippi Category:National Register of Historic Places in Yazoo County, Mississippi
title: Rosedale Plantation
